<div id="review_2005181601" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2005181601" />
    <a title="Monique Pearson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/21902909-monique-pearson"><img alt="Monique Pearson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1469442064p2/21902909.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2005181601?book_show_action=true">May 20, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Monique Pearson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Monique Pearson" href="/user/show/21902909-monique-pearson">Monique Pearson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2005181601" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3371208675091926787">Brand new author to me. I honestly mostly picked this book because of the title and cover, then the blurb tipped the scale. <br/>I was NOT disappointed! LOVED the story. LOVED the relationship between Gemma and her customers, especially her relationship with her overweight and cynical client. The descriptions of how a person becomes overweight, the assumptions people make about those individuals, and the fear of failure is so completely on point!<br/>Besides the honest emotional scenes this is a light, en</span>
  <span id="freeText3371208675091926787" style="display:none">Brand new author to me. I honestly mostly picked this book because of the title and cover, then the blurb tipped the scale. <br />I was NOT disappointed! LOVED the story. LOVED the relationship between Gemma and her customers, especially her relationship with her overweight and cynical client. The descriptions of how a person becomes overweight, the assumptions people make about those individuals, and the fear of failure is so completely on point!<br />Besides the honest emotional scenes this is a light, entertaining read. Harbison's humor is right up my alley. Can't wait to read more!</span>
